

# Django University - CS-405 Course Website

A professional, multi-page static website for teaching Django web development to university students. Built with modern web technologies and designed specifically for academic environments.

![Django University](https://img.shields.io/badge/Django-University-green?style=for-the-badge&logo=django)
![Course](https://img.shields.io/badge/Course-CS--405-blue?style=for-the-badge)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Active-success?style=for-the-badge)

## 📚 Overview

Django University is a comprehensive course platform designed for **Sophonie.dev: Web Development with Django**. The site provides a complete learning management experience including lectures, assignments, resources, and progress tracking.

### Key Features

- **📖 Structured Curriculum**: 16-week course with 6 modules covering Django fundamentals to production deployment
- **🎥 Video Integration**: Embedded lecture videos with downloadable transcripts and slides
- **📋 Assignment Management**: GitHub Classroom integration with submission tracking and grading
- **📚 Resource Library**: Curated documentation links, tools, and reading materials
- **📊 Progress Tracking**: Visual progress indicators and grade monitoring
- **📱 Responsive Design**: Fully mobile-responsive interface for learning on any device
- **🎨 Modern UI**: Glass morphism design with dark mode aesthetic

## 🗂️ Project Structure

```
django-university/
├── index.html                 # Course landing page / dashboard
├── syllabus.html             # Detailed 16-week course syllabus
├── assignments.html          # Assignment submission and tracking
├── resources.html            # Documentation, tools, and materials
├── lessons/
│   ├── index.html           # Lesson directory by module
│   └── module1/
│       ├── lesson1.html     # Individual lesson template
│       ├── lesson2.html     # Environment setup
│       └── lesson3.html     # First project
├── README.md                # This file
└── assets/                  # (Optional) Images, CSS, JS files
```

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Local web server (optional, for development)
- Git (for cloning and GitHub Classroom integration)

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/sophonie-1/django-university.git
   cd cs-405-django
   ```

2. **Open in browser**
   
   **Option A: Direct file access**
   - Open `index.html` in your web browser
   
   **Option B: Local server (recommended)**
   ```bash
   # Python 3
   python -m http.server 8000
   
   # Node.js (if installed)
   npx serve .
   
   # PHP
   php -S localhost:8000
   ```
   
   Then navigate to `http://localhost:8000`

3. **Customize for your institution**
   - Update instructor information in `index.html`
   - Modify course schedule dates in `syllabus.html`
   - Add your GitHub Classroom links in `assignments.html`
   - Update office hours and contact details

## 📋 Course Modules

| Module | Topic | Weeks | Key Concepts |
|--------|-------|-------|--------------|
| **01** | Introduction to Django | 1 | MTV Architecture, Setup, First Project |
| **02** | Models & Database Design | 2-3 | ORM, Relationships, Migrations, Queries |
| **03** | Views & URL Routing | 4-5 | Function/Class Views, URLconf, Middleware |
| **04** | Templates & Frontend | 6-7 | DTL, Static Files, Forms, Crispy Forms |
| **05** | Authentication & Security | 8-9 | User Auth, Permissions, CSRF, XSS Protection |
| **06** | REST APIs & Deployment | 10-16 | DRF, Testing, CI/CD, Docker, AWS/Heroku |

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3 (Tailwind CSS), Vanilla JavaScript
- **Icons**: [Lucide Icons](https://lucide.dev/)
- **Fonts**: Inter, JetBrains Mono (Google Fonts)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (via CDN)
- **No Backend Required**: Fully static site

## 📝 Customization Guide

### Changing Course Information

Edit `index.html`:
```html
<!-- Line ~45-50 -->
<span class="text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider">CS-405: Web Frameworks</span>

<!-- Line ~75-80 -->
<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6">
    CS-405: <br>
    <span class="gradient-text">Web Development</span><br>
    with Django
</h1>
```

### Updating Instructor Details

Edit `index.html` (around line ~180):
```html
<div>
    <p class="font-semibold">Dr. David Rodriguez</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Associate Professor</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Computer Science Dept.</p>
</div>
```

### Modifying Schedule Dates

Edit `syllabus.html` weekly cards:
```html
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Mar 16 - Mar 20</p>
<!-- Change to your academic calendar dates -->
```

### Adding GitHub Classroom Links

Edit `assignments.html`:
```html
<a href="YOUR_GITHUB_CLASSROOM_LINK" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white/10...">
    Access Repository
</a>
```

## 🎓 Academic Integration

### GitHub Classroom Setup

1. Create assignments in GitHub Classroom
2. Update links in `assignments.html`
3. Students fork repositories directly from assignment cards
4. Use GitHub Actions for autograding (optional)

### Learning Management System (LMS) Integration

This static site can be embedded in:
- **Canvas**: Upload as zip file or host externally
- **Blackboard**: Add as web link
- **Moodle**: Embed via iframe or link
- **GitHub Pages**: Host for free with custom domain

### Gradebook Integration

Currently manual, but can be extended with:
- Google Sheets API for grade display
- Canvas API integration
- Custom JSON file for grades

